	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><placeName>Chicago&#44; Ill.</placeName>&#44; <date>March 30&#44; 1865</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee> <placeName>Philada.</placeName></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Annexed please find a communication<lb/> for the Occident.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">In the last part of this communication a<lb/> topic is touched which might deserve<lb/> some earnest considerations from the Jewish<lb/> press.  My remarks are in an ironical<lb/> strain&#44; perhaps another contributor of your<lb/> periodical&#44; or its chief editor&#44; may deem it<lb/> proper to speak on it more earnestly and<lb/> thoroughly.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am&#44; dear sir&#44; in true regard</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your obd&#39;t serv&#39;t</p>
			<p rend="indent(3)"><persName role="author">B. Felsenthal</persName></p>
				<p>N. B. The word &#8222;sect&#44;&#8221; occurring several times<lb/> in the annexed communication&#44; has been made</p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p>use of with intention and purpose.  I would<lb/> request you not to strike out this expression.<lb/>  The truth indicated by this word &#40;viz&#58; that<lb/> Judaism in our days has divided into two sects&#41;.<lb/>  I am ready to defend at any time.  I<lb/> am well aware that many eminent men<lb/> in <placeName>Israel</placeName> will not consent to this assertion.<lb/>  Still I am convinced of its truth&#45;<lb/>fulness.</p>
		</body>
